    leaderNote: "Week 28 is the incarnation lesson — handle it with theological depth and pastoral warmth. The Logos word study is one of the richest in the curriculum, genuinely bridging Greek philosophy and Hebrew theology. The Augustine story is beloved and well-sourced (Confessions, Book 8) — the 'restless heart' quote is one of the most famous lines in Christian literature and many teens will immediately recognise the feeling it describes. Name it for them. The journal prompt (writing to the baby in the manger) is intentionally unusual and emotionally disarming — it invites personal connection with the incarnation rather than academic distance. Good lesson to revisit near the Christmas season if the curriculum runs through December.",
