    memoryVerse: "Simon Peter answered and said, Thou art the Christ, the Son of the living God. — Matthew 16:16",
    closingPrayer: "Lord Jesus — You asked the question that defines everything: 'Whom say ye that I am?' I say with Peter: You are the Christ, the Son of the living God. You are the Way — there is no other path to the Father. You are the Truth — everything else is measured by You. You are the Life — apart from You I have nothing that lasts. I confess it, I commit to it, and I ask for the Spirit's help to live it consistently — not just in words but in the shape of my days. Amen.",

    leaderNote: "Week 32 is the identity centrepiece of Term 3. The Lewis Trilemma is essential apologetics for this age group — teens encounter the 'great teacher' deflection constantly. Help them see that it is not intellectually honest, not based on the evidence. The Josh McDowell story is real and well-documented — his book 'Evidence That Demands a Verdict' is a good resource to point older teens toward. The discussion question about John 14:6 requires pastoral care — teens may have sincere friends of other faiths and need help articulating the exclusivity of Christ without contempt. The journal prompt is an evangelistic invitation: some teens who have not personally confessed Christ may do so for the first time this week. Create space and follow up.",
