    leaderNote: "Week 40 opens Term 4 by establishing the power source for everything that follows. The key theological move is distinguishing the Spirit as a Person (not a force or experience) and anchoring His work in consistent character transformation rather than dramatic phenomena alone. The Moody story is ideal for teens because it confronts the assumption that visible results equal Spirit-dependence. Invite honest sharing: where are students running on their own steam? The Parakletos concept — 'one called alongside' — often opens genuine vulnerability. This lesson sets up Week 41's community theme perfectly: Pentecost created not just Spirit-filled individuals but a Spirit-filled community.",
