      conclusion: "Unanswered prayer (in the specific sense we intended) is one of the hardest experiences in the Christian life, and it deserves honesty, not clichés. What we know: God hears every prayer (Psalm 34:15). God answers prayer according to His will and goodness (Romans 8:28). Some answers come in unexpected forms. Some come in the next generation. All of them come from a Father who is never indifferent. Hold the tension between honest lament and trusting surrender — Psalms of lament (Psalm 22, 77, 88) model exactly this.",
